docs.lead_paragraph: PUBLIC INSTITUTIONS. Excursion to Black well's Island, by Monsignor Bedini and the Ten Governors. At a late meeting of the Board of Governors, EDWARD C. WEST, President, SIMEON DRAPER, and P. McLAUGHLIN, Esqs., were appointed a Committee to invite His Excellency, Monsignor BEDINI, His Grace A rebbishop HUGMES, and others, to visit the Penitentiary and Charitable Institutions on Blackwell's Island.

docs.lead_paragraph: Attica, N. Y., is under embargo. One man has had small-pox and twenty others varioloid, and in consequence a Board of Health has been organized, and very stringent measures adopted to stop a further spread of the disease.

docs.lead_paragraph: This anxiously looked-for event came off Tuesday night with great eclat, at Musical Hall, on Bush-street. The spacious hall was appropriately decorated.. At one end was the banner of the Society of the "Sons of Erin," on which were painted the Harp of Erin, decked with shamrock, and enveloped in the American flag.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamer United States arrived here on Monday, the 15th. The steamer Medway, of the R. M. S. Packet Co., from Cathagena and St. Thomas, arrived at this port on the morning of the 16th. She brought a considerable force for the Panama Railroad Co.
